is. We find a steep bright-end slope\nof $\\beta\\approx-4.1$ and we can constrain the bright-end slope to\n$\\beta\\leq-3.4$ with $99\\%$ confidence. The density is well modeled by the\nexponential redshift evolution, resulting in a moderate decrease with redshift\n($\\gamma\\approx-0.4$).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Dec 2018 19:00:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-13"}
