 M^{-1.7}$ with a clearly defined truncation at an upper mass of $M_0\n\\sim 3 \\times 10^6~M_\\odot$, consistent with theoretical models of cloud\nformation controlled by stellar feedback and shear. Similarly, the cloud\npopulation shows a power-law distribution of size with $dN/dR \\propto R^{-2.8}$\nwith a truncation at $R_0 = 70$ pc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Dec 2018 20:52:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-19"}
